  "claim_boundary": [
    "This contract proves bounded live UEFI filesystem discovery and exact PBC1 and PKELF1 reads from deterministic development media.",
    "The fixed KERNEL.ELF path is an explicitly untrusted development path; the PBC1 manifest path is parsed but not opened, authenticated, or used to select the kernel.",
    "PKELF1 segments, BSS, and relative relocations are materialized in firmware-allocated pages and checked against the independent Python oracle.",
    "The returned r, rx, r, and rw mapping plan is validated with no writable-executable mapping, but no page tables or hardware permissions are installed.",
    "The loaded pages are released after hashing; no kernel page remains resident and no kernel entry point is called.",
    "PooleBoot closes all opened files, frees both file pools and all kernel pages, and treats cleanup failure as fatal before returning to firmware.",
    "No PBP1 live handoff is produced, no final memory-map retry occurs, and ExitBootServices is not called.",
    "No kernel or manifest authentication, Secure Boot enforcement, measured boot, TPM use, owner signature, or trust promotion is claimed.",
    "QEMU/OVMF evidence is a single-host non-promoting development result, not target-firmware or physical-hardware qualification.",
    "This does not satisfy the N5 exit gate, produce a bootable ISO, authorize signing or publication, or establish production readiness."
  ],
